   "id": "01d53abe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# My python findings while making a project"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "35d9a479-ea33-4d05-ab7a-5947b0001d6d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "use {.strip()} during input of numbers to remove the unwanted spaces that user usually gives\n",
    "and {.lower()} for all to be lowercase as\n",
    "\n",
    "input() catches: \"  ApPlE  \"\n",
    "\n",
    ".lower() turns it into: \"  apple  \"\n",
    "\n",
    ".strip() shaves off the ends to make it: \"apple\"\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "85bcebe9-aa15-403d-949a-baffd1c03128",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### While printing use f if you want the python to use their brain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "0436f8f2-551c-4fa5-a9aa-9f023c966622",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Hello {item}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Without the f:\n",
    "\n",
    "item = \"apple\"\n",
    "print(\"Hello {item}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "4e891475-ede4-408b-bb5b-22ad3fafa7b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Hello apple\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# With the f:\n",
    "print(f\"Hello {item}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
